---
// E1 (redesign spec 04) — SEO / answer-engine page #2: "What is a stablecoin depeg — and how fast does
// it happen?". USDC 2023 (SVB) case, the speed of it, and the RTMR real-time-monitoring angle. FAQ
// JSON-LD, snapshot CTA mid+end, internal links to monitoring/refusals/snapshot/packages. No fabricated
// numbers, no promised returns. Bilingual.
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Disclaimer from '../../components/Disclaimer.astro';

const faq = [
  {
    q: 'What is a stablecoin depeg?',
    a: 'A depeg is when a "stablecoin" trades away from its $1 target — say at $0.95 or $0.88. It means the market is pricing in a risk to the peg (reserve doubts, a broken mechanism, or a liquidity crunch). A "stablecoin" at $0.90 is not cash; it is a claim the market is discounting.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How fast does a depeg happen?',
    a: 'Fast — hours, sometimes minutes. USDC fell to about $0.87 within a day in March 2023 when ~$3.3B of its reserves were briefly stuck at the failing Silicon Valley Bank. It re-pegged after the deposits were guaranteed, but anyone who had to transact during that window faced a real, sudden loss.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do you protect against a depeg?',
    a: "You can't prevent one, but you can (1) diversify across issuers, (2) know each stablecoin's break condition, and (3) monitor the peg in real time so you can react. We run a real-time watchman that tracks stable pegs across a quorum of independent sources and de-risks automatically — the alternative is finding out from a headline.",
  },
];
const faqLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: faq.map((f) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })),
};
---
<Layout
  title="What is a stablecoin depeg — and how fast does it happen? | earn-defi.com"
  description="A stablecoin depeg is when a 'stablecoin' trades away from $1 — and it happens in hours, not weeks. The USDC 2023 case (SVB, ~$0.87 in a day) shows how fast. Here's what a depeg is, why it happens, and how a real-time risk desk watches for it. Not investment advice."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqLd)} />
  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-16 pb-24">
    <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-text-faint mb-4" data-ru="Разбор">The breakdown</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-5 leading-tight" data-ru="Что такое депег стейблкоина — и как быстро он происходит">What is a stablecoin depeg — and how fast does it happen?</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-8" data-ru="Депег — это когда «стейблкоин» торгуется в стороне от своего $1: например, по $0,95 или $0,88. И происходит это за часы, а не недели. Разберём, что это такое, почему случается и как за этим следит риск-деск в реальном времени.">
      A depeg is when a "stablecoin" trades away from its $1 target — say at $0.95 or $0.88. And it happens
      in hours, not weeks. Let's break down what it is, why it happens, and how a risk desk watches for it
      in real time.
    </p>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3" data-ru="Что это на самом деле значит">What it actually means</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-300 leading-relaxed" data-ru="«Стейблкоин» по $0,90 — это не доллар. Это требование, которое рынок дисконтирует: он закладывает риск к пегу — сомнения в резервах, сломанный механизм или нехватку ликвидности на выход. Балансовый экран показывает вам «1000 USDx = $1000». Цена на выходе может быть совсем другой. Именно этот разрыв — между балансовой и выходной стоимостью — мы и измеряем.">
        A "stablecoin" at $0.90 is not a dollar. It is a claim the market is discounting: it's pricing in a
        risk to the peg — reserve doubts, a broken mechanism, or an exit-liquidity crunch. Your balance
        screen shows "1000 USDx = $1000". The exit price can be a very different number. That gap — between
        book value and exit value — is exactly what we measure.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="rounded-xl p-5 my-8" style="background:rgba(52,211,153,.06);border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,.25)">
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-3" data-ru="Хотите знать, какие ваши стейблы уязвимее к депегу? Пройдите честный 60-секундный снимок — без кошелька, без email.">Want to know which of your stables are more exposed to a depeg? Take the honest 60-second snapshot — no wallet, no email.</p>
      <a href="/snapshot?src=learn" data-track="learn_cta_click" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-accent-500 hover:bg-accent-400 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors" data-ru="Пройти снимок →">Take the snapshot →</a>
    </div>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3" data-ru="Как быстро: кейс USDC 2023">How fast: the USDC 2023 case</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-300 leading-relaxed" data-ru="В марте 2023 USDC упал примерно до $0,87 за один день, когда ~$3,3 млрд его резервов кратко застряли в рушащемся Silicon Valley Bank. Он вернулся к пегу после гарантии по депозитам — но любому, кому пришлось транзакции в это окно, разрыв стоил реальных денег. Мораль: депег — это не медленное сползание, это обрыв за часы. Реагировать нужно ДО, а не читать про это постфактум.">
        In March 2023, USDC fell to about $0.87 in a single day when ~$3.3B of its reserves were briefly
        stuck at the failing Silicon Valley Bank. It re-pegged once deposits were guaranteed — but anyone
        who had to transact during that window paid a real cost. The lesson: a depeg is not a slow slide,
        it's a cliff over hours. You react before it — you don't read about it after.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-3">
        <a href="/monitoring" data-track="learn_to_monitoring" class="text-sm text-accent-400 underline" data-ru="Живой мониторинг пега (RTMR) →">Live peg monitoring (RTMR) →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3" data-ru="Как за этим следят честно">How you watch for it, honestly</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-300 leading-relaxed" data-ru="Наш real-time сторож (RTMR) следит за пегом стейблов по кворуму 5–10 независимых keyless-источников и снижает риск между дневными циклами — детерминированно, без ИИ в риске, fail-closed (расхождение источников = осторожность, не игнор). И мы отказываемся от стратегий, где доход — лишь компенсация за депег-хвост. Наша грань — измерять то, что другие не видят, и публиковать это.">
        Our real-time watchman (RTMR) tracks stable pegs across a quorum of 5–10 independent keyless sources
        and de-risks between daily cycles — deterministic, no AI in the risk path, fail-closed (sources
        disagreeing means caution, not ignoring it). And we refuse strategies whose yield is just
        depeg-tail compensation. Our edge is measuring what others don't see — and publishing it.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-3">
        <a href="/refusals" data-track="learn_to_refusals" class="text-sm text-accent-400 underline" data-ru="Журнал отказов →">The refusal log →</a>
        <a href="/how-we-think" data-track="learn_to_bridge" class="text-sm text-accent-400 underline" data-ru="Наша честная рамка →">Our honest frame →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4" data-ru="Частые вопросы">FAQ</h2>
      {faq.map((f) => (
        <details class="mb-3 rounded-lg p-4" style="background:var(--bg-surface);border:1px solid var(--border)">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white list-none">{f.q}</summary>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mt-2">{f.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </section>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-accent-500/20 bg-accent-500/[0.04] p-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-4" data-ru="Хотите честный взгляд на свои стейблы — без обещаний доходности?">Want an honest look at your own stables — with no promised returns?</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/snapshot?src=learn" data-track="learn_cta_click" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-accent-500 hover:bg-accent-400 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors" data-ru="60-секундный снимок →">60-second snapshot →</a>
        <a href="/packages" data-track="learn_to_packages" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-white/15 text-white text-sm font-medium hover:border-white/30 transition-colors" data-ru="Три честных тира →">The three honest tiers →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Disclaimer />

  <script is:inline>
    (function(){ try{ if(window.spaTrack) window.spaTrack('learn_view'); }catch(e){} })();
  </script>
</Layout>
